Bukit Asam, Medco, Unilever Indonesia: Indonesia Equity Preview

-- B y   B e r n i   M o e s t a f a
-- 
2011-06-10T01:39:34Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-06-10/bukit-asam-medco-unilever-indonesia-indonesia-equity-preview.html
Shares of the following companies
may have unusual moves in Indonesian trading. Stock symbols are
in parentheses, and share prices are as of the previous close.  The  Jakarta Composite index (JCI)  fell 0.5 percent to 3,806.19.  Energy companies: Crude oil futures rose for a fourth day,
gaining as much as 0.2 percent to $102.14 a barrel in after-
hours trading in  New York  as of 7:56 a.m. Jakarta time.  PT Energi Mega Persada (ENRG IJ),  Indonesia ’s second-
largest listed oil company, rose 2.4 percent to 210 rupiah and
PT Benakat Petroleum Energy (BIPI IJ) declined 2.4 percent to
121 rupiah.  PT Medco Energi Internasional (MEDC IJ): Indonesia’s
biggest listed oil company received $35 million as a settlement
for receivables after selling drilling company PT Apexindo
Pratama Duta to PT Mitra International Resources (MIRA IJ) in
2008, Medco said. Mitra originally owed Medco $68.2 million in
the form of guaranteed secured bonds as part of the A$340.89
million ($362 million) payment for buying Apexindo, the company
said. Medco fell 2.9 percent to 2,475 rupiah and Mitra declined
0.6 percent to 169 rupiah.  PT Tambang Batubara Bukit Asam (PTBA IJ): Indonesia’s
state-owned coal producer targets 100 percent growth in net
income this year to 4 trillion rupiah ($469 million) because of
an increase in coal demand and higher prices for domestic supply
contracts,  Bisnis Indonesia  reported, citing President Director
Sukrisno. Bukit Asam slipped 0.2 percent to 20,950 rupiah.  PT Unilever Indonesia (UNVR IJ): Unilever plans to relocate
a soap plant in  Germany  to Indonesia from where the products
will be sold to other Southeast Asian markets as well, Bisnis
Indonesia reported, citing Indonesia’s Industry Minister Mohamad Hidayat. Unilever Indonesia dropped 0.7 percent to 14,700 rupiah.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Berni Moestafa in Jakarta at 
 bmoestafa@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Darren Boey at   dboey@bloomberg.net  